<subSubSection id="4BE74DEB4C72FF85FED9FC8B6C50FC68" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="03421E604C72FF85FED9FC8B6C50FC68" blockId="20.[264,1323,873,980]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="3189C2724C72FF85FED9FC8B6E0AFC3F" bold="true" box="[264,378,873,899]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks</emphasis>
: The status of 
<taxonomicName id="C4FD65E34C72FF85FDF7FC886DC7FC3F" box="[550,695,874,899]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Bombylella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auricoma">
<emphasis id="3189C2724C72FF85FDF7FC886DC7FC3F" box="[550,695,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">B. auricoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not in doubt. It is readily identified as the only species of the genus with predominantly yellow hair and gold depressed hair­like scales on the dorsal surface of the thorax and abdomen.
</paragraph>
